sql:
SELECT DISTINCT day_of_week
FROM bus_schedules
WHERE route_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- Peak hours are typically the morning (8:00 AM - 10:00 AM) and evening (5:00 PM - 7:00 PM) rush hours;
- The cumulative frequency is calculated by summing the average frequency values of bus routes within the same peak hours count;
- The query focuses on identifying the most frequently used bus routes during these peak hours.

- A "top-level bus route" refers to routes that are not part of any schedules and are considered the root of the hierarchy;
- "Missing schedule" means there are no stops associated with the route in the schedule data;
- "Missing performance data" means there is no average speed recorded for the route.
